WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:50.130 --> 00:00:52.590
-Is it a girl?
- Yes.

3
00:00:52.670 --> 00:00:54.380
Show me its arm.

4
00:00:54.470 --> 00:00:57.340
- She bears the mark.
- No!

5
00:01:00.010 --> 00:01:03.520
The omen is true.
I must tell my mother.

6
00:01:05.940 --> 00:01:08.060
- Help me!
- I can't.

7
00:01:08.150 --> 00:01:10.940
- They're going to kill her.

8
00:01:18.820 --> 00:01:23.370
Oh. thank you. Ethna. Thank you.

9
00:01:31.880 --> 00:01:34.460
Stand aside for Queen Bavmorda!

10
00:01:58.820 --> 00:02:01.320
You cannot
stop the prophecy!

11
00:02:01.410 --> 00:02:04.330
This child will have no power over me.
Start the ritual.

12
00:02:04.410 --> 00:02:09.250
- No. No!
- Where's the baby?

13
00:02:09.330 --> 00:02:11.750
The midwife.
Find that baby. Sorsha.

14
00:02:11.840 --> 00:02:15.210
Use the dogs.
Bring her back to me alive!

15
00:02:15.260 --> 00:02:17.380
Your reign of terror
is at an end!

16
00:02:17.470 --> 00:02:19.550
She will come back.
and she will finish you!

17
00:02:19.630 --> 00:02:23.220
- Silence. wench.
- My baby will finish you!
- Kill her.

18
00:05:50.430 --> 00:05:52.430
Dada! Dada!

19
00:05:55.850 --> 00:05:59.150
-Dada! Dada!
- Whoa! Whoa!

20
00:06:00.400 --> 00:06:03.650
Dada! Dada!
We found something in the river.

21
00:06:03.690 --> 00:06:05.650
I can't run off and play
with you now. Ranon.

22
00:06:05.690 --> 00:06:07.990
- I've got work to do.
- You gotta come. Hurry!

23
00:06:12.990 --> 00:06:15.540
Come on.

24
00:06:17.870 --> 00:06:20.920
Don't go near it.
We don't know where it's been.

25
00:06:21.000 --> 00:06:23.920
But. Dada. it's a baby.

26
00:06:24.000 --> 00:06:28.800
- It's not like us.
- No. It's not a Nelwyn.

27
00:06:28.880 --> 00:06:32.430
- It looks like a Daikini baby.
- What's a Daikini?

28
00:06:32.510 --> 00:06:34.850
Daikinis are big.

29
00:06:34.890 --> 00:06:38.020
- Giants who live far away.

30
00:06:38.100 --> 00:06:40.400
Oh. she's so cute.

31
00:06:40.480 --> 00:06:44.520
- Can't we keep it. Dada?
- No!

32
00:06:44.570 --> 00:06:49.820
We'll push it downstream and forget
we ever saw it. Come on.

33
00:06:49.900 --> 00:06:51.820
- Come on.
- Ufgood! Willow Ufgood!

34
00:06:51.870 --> 00:06:56.040
Shhh! It's the prefect.
That's all I need.

35
00:06:56.120 --> 00:06:59.580
Keep it quiet.
Don't touch it.

36
00:07:01.120 --> 00:07:04.960
Mr. Burglekutt. my husband
hasn't stolen anything!

37
00:07:05.050 --> 00:07:07.010
Baaa!

38
00:07:10.430 --> 00:07:13.930
Ufgood. you still haven't
paid your debts to me.

39
00:07:14.010 --> 00:07:16.010
Where did you
get these seeds?

40
00:07:16.100 --> 00:07:18.850
Well. maybe I used magic.

41
00:07:18.930 --> 00:07:22.850
You're no sorcerer. Ufgood.
You're a clown.

42
00:07:22.940 --> 00:07:26.520
I sell the planting seeds around here.
Now tell me where you got them.

43
00:07:26.570 --> 00:07:30.030
My family's been gathering them
in the forest since last fall.

44
00:07:30.110 --> 00:07:33.160
- There's no law against that.

45
00:07:33.240 --> 00:07:38.410
Willow. you didn't leave
them alone by the river?

46
00:07:38.450 --> 00:07:40.790
Magic?
You'll need magic...

47
00:07:40.870 --> 00:07:43.250
if you expect to get your planting
done before the rains start.

48
00:07:45.290 --> 00:07:50.800
I will have this land. And you're
gonna end up working in the mines.

49
00:07:53.010 --> 00:07:56.760
- Baaa-

50
00:07:59.890 --> 00:08:02.890
Oh. you're lovely.

51
00:08:02.940 --> 00:08:04.940
- Yes. you are.

52
00:08:05.020 --> 00:08:09.480
- Kiaya!
- Oh. Willow!

53
00:08:09.530 --> 00:08:14.450
- Good girl. Good girl.
- Under no condition whatsoever...

54
00:08:14.530 --> 00:08:17.280
is anyone in this family
to fall in love with that baby.

55
00:08:17.330 --> 00:08:22.080
Yes. you are. Come on. Mims.
Come on. Come on.

56
00:08:22.160 --> 00:08:24.210
There we are. Come on.

57
00:08:24.290 --> 00:08:26.920
Hey. I will not be ignored!

58
00:08:27.000 --> 00:08:30.670
Mims? Ranon?

59
00:08:41.680 --> 00:08:43.810
- You're gonna be all clean.

60
00:08:50.480 --> 00:08:53.780
Willow. do you think we should
take her to the village council?

61
00:08:53.860 --> 00:08:56.450
No. No.
They'll think it's a bad omen.

62
00:08:56.530 --> 00:08:59.330
There'll be a flood or a drought.
and everyone will blame me for it.

63
00:08:59.410 --> 00:09:02.330
"Willow Ufgood brought around
that Daikini. didn't he?

64
00:09:02.370 --> 00:09:05.420
That's right. He's that
lousy farmer too. Let's get him!

65
00:09:05.500 --> 00:09:09.540
- Willow. calm down.
- Calm down?

66
00:09:09.630 --> 00:09:11.670
Kiaya. tomorrow's my big day.

67
00:09:11.760 --> 00:09:15.510
Love. the High Aldwin hasn't
picked a new apprentice in years.

68
00:09:15.550 --> 00:09:18.850
Tomorrow's gonna be different.
I just know he's gonna pick me.

69
00:09:21.600 --> 00:09:25.270
- Here. Hold her.
- Hey. no. I don't want her. Kiaya.

70
00:09:25.350 --> 00:09:28.150
- Hold her while I get some milk.
- Oh. no. no. Oh.

71
00:09:35.780 --> 00:09:39.240
- Dada. she likes you.

72
00:09:46.250 --> 00:09:47.420
- Bye.

73
00:09:47.420 --> 00:09:50.540
- Bye.

74
00:09:50.590 --> 00:09:54.510
- Come on. kids. Let's go.

75
00:10:00.550 --> 00:10:04.140
I will now magic ally join the rings!

76
00:10:26.120 --> 00:10:28.710
- Whoa-ah!

77
00:10:33.500 --> 00:10:35.920
Thank you. son.

78
00:10:35.960 --> 00:10:41.010
If you're easily shocked.
please turn away.

79
00:10:56.190 --> 00:10:58.450
Give me a ripe one. Good.

80
00:11:04.660 --> 00:11:09.160
- And now. for my final amazing feat.

81
00:11:09.250 --> 00:11:14.090
- I will make this entire pig disappear!

82
00:11:22.140 --> 00:11:27.270
- Mims. see?
- Please. watch very closely.

83
00:11:27.350 --> 00:11:32.980
- Wuppitybairn. deru. deru!

84
00:11:35.230 --> 00:11:37.650
- Well-
- What happened to your pig?

85
00:11:40.360 --> 00:11:43.410
No!
Hey. come here. you!

86
00:11:47.830 --> 00:11:51.250
I had seen enough.

87
00:12:06.350 --> 00:12:09.640
Attention!
The High Aldwin...

88
00:12:09.720 --> 00:12:12.640
-will now make his choice
for his new apprentice!
- You'll be all right.

89
00:12:12.690 --> 00:12:16.150
Bring forth the hopefuls.

90
00:12:16.230 --> 00:12:18.650
- Good luck.
- Good luck. Dada.

91
00:12:18.730 --> 00:12:22.490
Willow Ufgood. a hopeful?
How did he get picked?

92
00:12:22.570 --> 00:12:25.030
Is this a joke?

93
00:12:25.120 --> 00:12:29.580
- Willow?

94
00:12:32.000 --> 00:12:37.460
Magic is the bloodstream
of the universe!

95
00:12:37.500 --> 00:12:42.090
Forget all you know...
or think you know.

96
00:12:42.170 --> 00:12:46.180
All that your require
is your intuition.

97
00:12:46.260 --> 00:12:50.350
Now. the power
to control the world...

98
00:12:50.430 --> 00:12:54.940
is in which finger?

99
00:13:36.900 --> 00:13:41.440
- No apprentice this year!

100
00:14:01.840 --> 00:14:05.220
- Where's Mims?
- I don't know. She was right here!

101
00:14:05.300 --> 00:14:08.220
Take Ranon in there. quick!

102
00:14:16.100 --> 00:14:19.060
- Mims!

103
00:14:20.440 --> 00:14:22.570
- Mims!

104
00:14:30.820 --> 00:14:35.660
- Mims!
- Dada-

105
00:14:36.910 --> 00:14:40.000
- I'm scared. Dada!

106
00:14:50.300 --> 00:14:52.890
Come on!

107
00:15:10.530 --> 00:15:13.490
- Vohnkar!

108
00:15:23.000 --> 00:15:25.920
- Check to make sure.
- It's dead!

109
00:15:28.260 --> 00:15:30.050
Dada! Dada!

110
00:15:33.390 --> 00:15:35.640
It was looking
for somebody's baby!

111
00:15:38.680 --> 00:15:42.480
- Mommy.
- Kiaya!

112
00:15:49.860 --> 00:15:53.200
Kiaya!
Kiaya!

113
00:15:53.280 --> 00:15:56.280
- I'm here.

114
00:16:00.370 --> 00:16:04.000
- Oh. Kiaya.

115
00:16:04.080 --> 00:16:06.290
We can't keep
the baby. Kiaya.

116
00:16:06.340 --> 00:16:09.210
We have to take her
to the village council.

117
00:16:22.690 --> 00:16:27.610
Silence! One beast we can kill.
but there may be more.

118
00:16:27.690 --> 00:16:30.070
And you can be assured
that they won't give up...

119
00:16:30.150 --> 00:16:32.110
until they find what
they're looking for!

120
00:16:32.200 --> 00:16:35.450
-It's a sign!
- Who's to blame for this?

121
00:16:35.530 --> 00:16:38.030
We must find the culprit
and throw him in the pit!

122
00:16:38.080 --> 00:16:43.210
- In the pit! In the pit!

123
00:16:43.290 --> 00:16:45.420
In the pit! In the pit!

124
00:16:45.500 --> 00:16:48.800
-In the pit! In the pit!
- Willow.

125
00:16:48.880 --> 00:16:53.220
- Willow Ufgood.

126
00:16:53.300 --> 00:16:55.760
Come forward.

127
00:17:01.430 --> 00:17:06.770
My children found this baby
alone by the river. High Aldwin.

128
00:17:12.360 --> 00:17:14.530
- A Daikini child.

129
00:17:14.610 --> 00:17:17.820
That's what the beasts want.
Let's give it back to them!

130
00:17:17.910 --> 00:17:18.990
Yeah!

131
00:17:19.080 --> 00:17:22.370
- They'll kill her! You can't!
- It isn't one of us.

132
00:17:22.450 --> 00:17:25.080
This child is special!

133
00:17:25.170 --> 00:17:29.460
This child must be taken beyond
the boundaries of our village.

134
00:17:29.540 --> 00:17:32.590
All the way across
the great river...

135
00:17:32.670 --> 00:17:34.760
to the Daikini crossroads.

136
00:17:34.840 --> 00:17:39.550
- Well. who'll do that?
- It seems only fair...

137
00:17:39.600 --> 00:17:42.970
that the man to take
this baby to the crossroads...

138
00:17:43.060 --> 00:17:46.020
be the very man who
plucked it out of the river.

139
00:17:47.600 --> 00:17:50.230
- I nominate Willow Ufgood.

140
00:17:50.270 --> 00:17:52.820
No!

141
00:17:52.900 --> 00:17:56.450
I will consult the bones!

142
00:18:03.830 --> 00:18:09.330
- The bones tell me... nothing.

143
00:18:11.000 --> 00:18:14.920
Do you have any love
for this child?

144
00:18:23.350 --> 00:18:27.810
Yes. Yes. I do.

145
00:18:27.890 --> 00:18:32.320
- The bones have spoken!

146
00:18:32.360 --> 00:18:36.320
Willow Ufgood. the safety
of this village depends upon you.

147
00:18:36.400 --> 00:18:40.490
- Praise the bones!
- Praise the bones!

148
00:18:40.570 --> 00:18:43.080
But you will need help.

149
00:18:43.160 --> 00:18:48.500
Who has the courage to protect
our brave fellow on his journey?

150
00:18:50.540 --> 00:18:54.670
- I'll go with him.
- Ah. Meegosh.

151
00:18:54.710 --> 00:18:58.010
- Excellent choice.
- I'll go!

152
00:18:58.090 --> 00:19:00.550
Vohnkar! Vohnkar!

153
00:19:00.640 --> 00:19:03.350
No! Not vohnkar!
He's the best warrior in the village!

154
00:19:03.390 --> 00:19:06.600
We need him here!
Vohnkar. step back!

155
00:19:14.610 --> 00:19:17.190
All this expedition needs
is a leader.

156
00:19:17.280 --> 00:19:20.660
And according to the bones...

157
00:19:20.740 --> 00:19:24.120
- Bh-
-That leader is...

158
00:19:24.200 --> 00:19:25.620
...you. Burglekutt!

159
00:19:25.620 --> 00:19:26.620
you. Burglekutt!

160
00:19:26.700 --> 00:19:30.170
vohnkar!

161
00:19:30.250 --> 00:19:34.340
- What's your problem. son?
- How do you mean?

162
00:19:34.420 --> 00:19:39.720
When I held up my fingers
what was your first impulse?

163
00:19:39.800 --> 00:19:43.720
- Well. it was stupid.
-Just tell me.

164
00:19:43.760 --> 00:19:48.220
- To pick my own finger.
- Aha! That was the correct answer.

165
00:19:48.310 --> 00:19:53.060
You lack faith in yourself.
More than anyone in the village.

166
00:19:53.100 --> 00:19:55.730
you have the potential
to be a great sorcerer.

167
00:19:55.820 --> 00:20:00.650
Now. when you're out there.
listen to your own heart.

168
00:20:02.610 --> 00:20:07.620
- These will protect you. They're magic!
- Acorns?

169
00:20:07.700 --> 00:20:11.710
Anything you throw them at
turns to stone.

170
00:20:14.790 --> 00:20:18.000
You have much to learn.
young Ufgood.

171
00:20:30.930 --> 00:20:35.400
- Are you scared. Dada?
- No!

172
00:20:35.480 --> 00:20:39.730
Even with fairies in the woods that'll
put you to sleep for a hundred years?

173
00:20:41.740 --> 00:20:43.860
- Doesn't bother me.
- Brownies?

174
00:20:43.950 --> 00:20:46.870
- Dragons?
- Trolls?

175
00:20:46.950 --> 00:20:50.370
Trolls that'll skin you alive
and take your face off?

176
00:20:50.450 --> 00:20:54.080
Ranon!
You know I hate trolls.

177
00:20:54.120 --> 00:20:57.290
I can be your guard
and carry your spear.

178
00:20:57.340 --> 00:20:58.920
Me too. Me too. Dada.

179
00:21:00.510 --> 00:21:05.840
What a lucky father I am. I wish
I could take you bobbins with me.

180
00:21:08.930 --> 00:21:11.470
Good-bye. Dada.

181
00:21:13.520 --> 00:21:17.520
Go play!
Go on.

182
00:21:21.480 --> 00:21:25.030
We've never been apart.

183
00:21:26.070 --> 00:21:29.410
I miss you already.

184
00:21:30.740 --> 00:21:34.160
Don't worry. Kiaya.
I'll be fine.

185
00:21:34.250 --> 00:21:36.170
I'll be back
before you know it.

186
00:21:38.420 --> 00:21:41.170
Well. remember
to keep her warm.

187
00:21:43.210 --> 00:21:45.930
And... here.

188
00:21:48.050 --> 00:21:50.850
This will bring you luck.

189
00:22:04.030 --> 00:22:06.360
Good brave people!

190
00:22:08.200 --> 00:22:10.950
The outer world is
no place for a Nelwyn.

191
00:22:11.030 --> 00:22:15.750
Give the baby to the first
Daikini you see. then hurry home.

192
00:22:19.250 --> 00:22:22.840
Tuatha...
lokwathrak... tuatha!

193
00:22:22.920 --> 00:22:26.470
Going the direction the bird is flying!

194
00:22:26.550 --> 00:22:30.470
- Ooh.

195
00:22:30.550 --> 00:22:33.390
It's going back to the village!

196
00:22:35.230 --> 00:22:37.190
Ignore the bird.
Follow the river.

197
00:22:37.270 --> 00:22:39.520
Move out!

198
00:23:03.460 --> 00:23:06.920
- Hold on. Meegosh.
- What's wrong?

199
00:23:07.010 --> 00:23:11.050
- We have to stop.
- Stop? Why?

200
00:23:11.090 --> 00:23:13.600
- The baby's sick.

201
00:23:17.560 --> 00:23:22.150
She's not sick!
Let me see.

202
00:23:22.230 --> 00:23:25.440
Uhaghh!
Take her! Take her!

203
00:23:28.030 --> 00:23:31.110
She'll be fine
once she gets some rest.

204
00:23:33.450 --> 00:23:35.120
Clean me up.

205
00:23:38.790 --> 00:23:42.000
I didn't ask you
to bring me a dead nursemaid.

206
00:23:42.080 --> 00:23:46.000
-Sorsha. you're useless!
-I'm backtracking the nursemaid's trail.

207
00:23:46.050 --> 00:23:48.260
I'll find where
she hid the baby.

208
00:23:50.220 --> 00:23:52.470
Ah. General Kael. at last.

209
00:23:52.550 --> 00:23:57.270
My queen. I have destroyed
the castle at Galladoorn.

210
00:23:57.350 --> 00:24:01.060
Well done. But now I have
another task for you.

211
00:24:01.140 --> 00:24:06.610
Help my daughter to find
that tiny. helpless baby...

212
00:24:06.690 --> 00:24:08.650
that continues
somehow to elude her.

213
00:24:10.570 --> 00:24:12.530
The baby of the prophecy?

214
00:24:12.610 --> 00:24:16.030
- The one that would destroy you?
- I need that baby alive.

215
00:24:16.120 --> 00:24:18.580
I must perform
the ritual that will...

216
00:24:18.660 --> 00:24:22.000
exile the child's spirit
into oblivion.

217
00:24:22.080 --> 00:24:24.830
- Find her!
- I don't need his help. Mother.

218
00:24:24.880 --> 00:24:26.960
You'll do as I say. child.

219
00:24:33.390 --> 00:24:35.550
I read the signs.

220
00:24:35.640 --> 00:24:38.810
One day. I fear. your daughter
will betray you.

221
00:24:38.890 --> 00:24:43.060
I trust her loyalty
more than I trust yours.

222
00:24:58.790 --> 00:25:01.330
- Move!

223
00:25:01.410 --> 00:25:03.370
It's an ambush.
Come on. Move!

224
00:25:07.670 --> 00:25:11.380
- Come on!

225
00:25:20.970 --> 00:25:23.890
The Nelwyns have got the baby.
We've searched the village.

226
00:25:23.980 --> 00:25:26.940
But a group of them
Is on the road somewhere.

227
00:25:27.020 --> 00:25:28.860
They couldn' t have gone far!

228
00:25:28.900 --> 00:25:31.900
Widen the search
and report to Sorsha!

229
00:25:39.280 --> 00:25:42.000
Come. We'll keep to the woods.

230
00:26:20.780 --> 00:26:24.950
That's it!
It's the crossroads!

231
00:26:41.390 --> 00:26:44.350
Keep this fire high.
We don't know what's out there.

232
00:26:49.850 --> 00:26:52.360
- What was that?

233
00:26:53.690 --> 00:26:56.490
Get the spears!

234
00:27:12.920 --> 00:27:14.880
- Uhh. Uhh.

235
00:27:14.920 --> 00:27:18.800
Give me some water. peck.
or you die.

236
00:27:18.880 --> 00:27:21.300
Do you understand?

237
00:27:21.390 --> 00:27:23.260
- Water.
- Yeah.

238
00:27:25.390 --> 00:27:27.390
Hurry up!

239
00:27:31.400 --> 00:27:34.320
Get me some water.
you measly little pecks.

240
00:27:34.400 --> 00:27:37.860
It's a Daikini.
We're in luck.

241
00:27:37.940 --> 00:27:40.360
We can't give her to him!

242
00:27:40.410 --> 00:27:44.370
- Somebody put him there for a reason.
- We've got to get rid of her.

243
00:27:44.450 --> 00:27:47.040
- Those soldiers are after us.
- Shhh.

244
00:27:47.120 --> 00:27:50.000
He's looking right at us.

245
00:27:53.920 --> 00:27:55.920
We've got to give
that baby to somebody.

246
00:27:55.960 --> 00:27:58.840
I'm somebody.

247
00:27:58.920 --> 00:28:03.260
Let me out of here. I'll take care
of the baby. 

248
00:28:05.100 --> 00:28:09.730
- I trust him completely.
- But he tried to strangle me.

249
00:28:09.770 --> 00:28:13.730
- I want to go home!
- No. Burglekutt!

250
00:28:13.810 --> 00:28:17.150
- We should wait!
- Are you challenging my authority?

251
00:28:17.230 --> 00:28:20.610
As far as this baby
is concerned... yes.

252
00:28:20.650 --> 00:28:23.700
Don't listen to him. Burglekutt.

253
00:28:23.780 --> 00:28:28.870
Fine. You stay here alone.
but we're going.

254
00:28:28.950 --> 00:28:31.160
That's a bad idea.
Very bad.

255
00:28:31.250 --> 00:28:34.670
- Dangerous out there.
- Get the gear. men.

256
00:28:34.750 --> 00:28:38.300
- vohnkar-
- It's not his decision!

257
00:28:38.380 --> 00:28:42.300
Burglekutt. you're troll dung.

258
00:28:42.380 --> 00:28:44.050
Don't let him
talk to you that way.

259
00:28:44.140 --> 00:28:46.220
Listen here. runt.

260
00:28:46.300 --> 00:28:50.270
While you're wasting time here.
your fields aren't getting planted.

261
00:28:50.350 --> 00:28:54.650
- Think about it!
- Burglekutt. I'm gonna-

262
00:28:54.730 --> 00:28:58.110
You're gonna what?

263
00:29:01.990 --> 00:29:04.570
Some day. Burglekutt.
Some day.

264
00:29:04.660 --> 00:29:06.660
Vohnkar. let's go!

265
00:29:10.330 --> 00:29:13.040
Meegosh. are you coming?

266
00:29:15.330 --> 00:29:18.920
- I'm staying.
- Come on. men.

267
00:29:19.000 --> 00:29:23.170
Burglekutt. Let me out of here.
I'll take care of the baby. I swear.

268
00:29:23.260 --> 00:29:25.930
just let me out of here.
Please!

269
00:29:26.010 --> 00:29:29.470
Vohnkar. let me borrow that spear...
just for a minute.

270
00:29:29.510 --> 00:29:31.810
Get-
Well. at least get me some water!

271
00:29:31.850 --> 00:29:36.810
Burglekutt. don't leave me alone
with these two! 

272
00:29:36.900 --> 00:29:41.690
- What'll we do now. Willow?

273
00:29:41.780 --> 00:29:44.400
Well. that was really stupid. peck.

274
00:29:44.490 --> 00:29:49.280
- Don't call me a peck.
- Oh. I'm sorry... peck.

275
00:29:49.370 --> 00:29:53.120
- Peck. peck. peck. peck.
- You be careful!

276
00:29:53.200 --> 00:29:56.960
I'm a powerful sorcerer.
See this acorn?

277
00:29:58.380 --> 00:30:02.880
- I'll throw it. and turn you to stone.
- Whoo-

278
00:30:02.960 --> 00:30:04.920
I'm really scared.

279
00:30:04.970 --> 00:30:07.840
No. don't! Don't!

280
00:30:07.890 --> 00:30:10.720
There's a peck here
with an acorn pointed at me!

281
00:30:10.810 --> 00:30:13.480
Oh. I wouldn't
want to waste it.

282
00:30:13.560 --> 00:30:16.810
Ha!
Peck. peck. peck. peck.

283
00:30:16.900 --> 00:30:19.440
peck. peck. peck.
peck. peck!

284
00:30:48.050 --> 00:30:50.930
- What was that?

285
00:30:54.310 --> 00:30:58.020
Mornin'. boys.

286
00:30:58.100 --> 00:31:02.230
Rough night last night.
wasn't it?

287
00:31:02.270 --> 00:31:05.650
I don't think I introduced
myself yesterday.

288
00:31:05.740 --> 00:31:09.200
My name is Madmartigan.
and you are. uh-

289
00:31:09.280 --> 00:31:12.240
No. Meegosh.
Don't go near him.

290
00:31:12.280 --> 00:31:15.750
- He's dangerous.
- I am not.

291
00:31:15.790 --> 00:31:17.960
Good.

292
00:31:22.710 --> 00:31:25.010
Stop! Wait!

293
00:31:26.760 --> 00:31:29.510
- Whoa!

294
00:31:34.970 --> 00:31:39.480
- What's going on?
- Smells like a battle.

295
00:31:39.560 --> 00:31:42.060
I suppose you're a warrior.

296
00:31:42.150 --> 00:31:44.650
I am the greatest swordsman
that ever lived.

297
00:31:44.730 --> 00:31:47.570
Humph.

298
00:31:47.650 --> 00:31:51.410
Say. uh- Could I have
some of that water?

299
00:32:01.120 --> 00:32:05.880
I don't know why I try.

300
00:32:10.680 --> 00:32:13.930
I guess I am gonna die here.
Who cares.

301
00:32:14.010 --> 00:32:15.930
- Here.
- Thanks. friend. Oh!

302
00:32:16.010 --> 00:32:18.390
- What's that?

303
00:32:18.480 --> 00:32:22.440
I'd say
two or three hundred horses.

304
00:32:22.520 --> 00:32:26.480
five or six wagons...
and about a thousand fools.

305
00:32:29.190 --> 00:32:32.990
- Thank you. Ohh-
- Come on. Meegosh.

306
00:32:37.330 --> 00:32:41.040
It's gonna be
all right. little bobbin.

307
00:32:47.000 --> 00:32:50.920
- Everything's gonna be all right.

308
00:32:54.260 --> 00:32:57.350
- Excuse me. sir.
- Out of the way. peck!

309
00:32:59.310 --> 00:33:01.690
Uh. pardon me.

310
00:33:01.730 --> 00:33:03.850
Uh-

311
00:33:09.480 --> 00:33:14.700
Excuse me. sir. We found one
of your babies in our village.

312
00:33:14.780 --> 00:33:17.700
Will you please
take care of her?

313
00:33:17.780 --> 00:33:22.210
We're going into battle. little ones.
Find a woman to take care of her.

314
00:33:23.620 --> 00:33:26.790
They thought you were
a woman. Airk.

315
00:33:26.880 --> 00:33:29.250
Well-

316
00:33:29.340 --> 00:33:33.880
-Madmartigan. what did you do this time?
-Nothing you wouldn't have done.

317
00:33:33.970 --> 00:33:36.340
I always knew
you'd end up in a crow's cage.

318
00:33:36.430 --> 00:33:38.260
At least I'm not
down there herding sheep.

319
00:33:38.350 --> 00:33:39.850
What are you doing this far north?

320
00:33:39.930 --> 00:33:41.930
The Nockmaar army
destroyed Galladoorn.

321
00:33:42.930 --> 00:33:44.270
The castle?

322
00:33:44.310 --> 00:33:46.770
Bavmorda's troops are
crushing everything in sight.

323
00:33:46.860 --> 00:33:48.770
Come on.
Let me out of here. Airk.

324
00:33:48.860 --> 00:33:51.110
Give me a sword.
I'll win this war for you.

325
00:33:51.230 --> 00:33:55.530
Madmartigan-
I still serve Galladoorn.

326
00:33:55.610 --> 00:33:57.570
You serve no one.

327
00:33:57.660 --> 00:33:59.910
Remember?

328
00:33:59.990 --> 00:34:03.200
Sit in your coffin and rot.

329
00:34:03.290 --> 00:34:06.330
- Hyah!
- Wait. Airk. You need me!

330
00:34:06.420 --> 00:34:08.840
I'll be around
long after you're dead!

331
00:34:08.920 --> 00:34:11.550
When I get out of here.
I'm gonna cut your head off...

332
00:34:11.630 --> 00:34:13.720
and stick it
on a pig pole!

333
00:34:31.230 --> 00:34:35.950
- I miss Kiaya and the bobbins.

334
00:34:39.950 --> 00:34:43.750
We're running out of food.

335
00:34:43.830 --> 00:34:47.460
Nobody's gonna
take care of that baby.

336
00:34:47.500 --> 00:34:50.500
You know why?
Nobody cares.

337
00:34:53.380 --> 00:34:56.930
Except me.

338
00:34:57.010 --> 00:35:01.220
You want to go back to your families.
I want out of this cage.

339
00:35:01.300 --> 00:35:05.270
Let me take care of that baby.
I'll look after her like she was my own.

340
00:35:05.350 --> 00:35:08.310
I believe he would. Willow.

341
00:35:08.400 --> 00:35:10.940
He doesn't know
anything about babies.

342
00:35:11.020 --> 00:35:16.240
Right. But I know
a lot of women who do.

343
00:35:16.320 --> 00:35:19.240
If I had somebody in my life.

344
00:35:19.320 --> 00:35:22.910
a little daughter. perhaps.

345
00:35:22.990 --> 00:35:26.250
I might have a reason
to go on living.

346
00:35:29.500 --> 00:35:32.290
You can't leave me
in here to die.

347
00:35:32.380 --> 00:35:35.420
Not when all I want
to do is protect her.

348
00:35:48.730 --> 00:35:52.650
I feel better!

349
00:35:52.730 --> 00:35:56.440
-You've done the right thing! -Okay. All right. All right.

350
00:35:56.530 --> 00:36:00.990
- You gotta promise to feed her.
- Come to Daddy. little darlin'.

351
00:36:01.070 --> 00:36:06.080
- And keep her clean.
- Absolutely.

352
00:36:06.160 --> 00:36:08.200
- Hee. hee. hee!

353
00:36:08.290 --> 00:36:13.170
- Wheee!

354
00:36:13.250 --> 00:36:16.500
She likes me.

355
00:36:18.590 --> 00:36:20.970
Here are her changing rags.

356
00:36:21.050 --> 00:36:23.260
- And her milk bladder.
- Any milk in there?

357
00:36:23.300 --> 00:36:27.600
- It's for her!
- I wouldn't steal from a baby.

358
00:36:29.310 --> 00:36:32.850
- You wory too much. peck.

359
00:36:32.940 --> 00:36:36.860
- It's Willow.
- I mean Willow.

360
00:36:36.940 --> 00:36:42.700
Now listen. boys- Willow.
You've done the right thing.

361
00:36:42.780 --> 00:36:46.160
And I want you to get home
and bring your crop in.

362
00:36:52.670 --> 00:36:56.920
- Good-bye. little one.

363
00:37:05.640 --> 00:37:07.890
Please. take good care of her.

364
00:37:09.680 --> 00:37:12.520
I give you my word of honor!

365
00:37:19.190 --> 00:37:23.110
- Meegosh. slow down!
- Oh. come on!

366
00:37:23.150 --> 00:37:27.410
If we hurry. we can be home by
tomorrow morning. We'll be heroes.

367
00:37:27.490 --> 00:37:31.000
- Do you really think so?
- Sure.

368
00:37:31.080 --> 00:37:33.330
"Look. there's
Willow and Meegosh.

369
00:37:33.420 --> 00:37:35.630
The heroes have come home."

370
00:37:35.710 --> 00:37:38.800
"Welcome back. boys.
You deserve medals!"

371
00:37:38.880 --> 00:37:43.130
- Yeah. Medals.

372
00:37:43.170 --> 00:37:46.930
Meegosh-

373
00:37:48.810 --> 00:37:52.930
- Did we do the right thing?
- Absolutely.

374
00:37:53.020 --> 00:37:57.310
- There's nothing to wory about.

375
00:38:00.320 --> 00:38:02.610
Hyah! Ha!

376
00:38:02.690 --> 00:38:07.910
I stole the baby! I stole the baby!

377
00:38:07.990 --> 00:38:11.750
- Hyah!
- That's my baby!

378
00:38:11.830 --> 00:38:13.790
- Stop! Wait! Come back!

379
00:38:13.870 --> 00:38:17.040
Left. you stupid bird.
Left! Ha ha!

380
00:38:19.840 --> 00:38:23.090
- Ah!
- Ow!

381
00:38:23.170 --> 00:38:26.840
Brownies!
Let's get out of here!

382
00:38:26.930 --> 00:38:30.260
- Come on. Meegosh!
- Ow!

383
00:38:31.260 --> 00:38:35.020
- Uhh-uh-huh-uh.
- Uhh. Oww!

384
00:38:36.310 --> 00:38:38.360
We'll outrun 'em!

385
00:38:43.110 --> 00:38:47.200
-Hey. ugly. wake up!- 

386
00:38:47.280 --> 00:38:49.740
Huh?

387
00:38:49.780 --> 00:38:54.910
- Stand your ground. He's our prisoner.

388
00:38:54.950 --> 00:38:57.750
Meegosh.
where's the baby?

389
00:38:57.790 --> 00:38:59.750
Bring the Nelwyns tome.

390
00:38:59.790 --> 00:39:01.210
All right. you heard her!

391
00:39:01.290 --> 00:39:05.090
- What's going on?
- Shut up. or I'll break your nose.

392
00:39:05.130 --> 00:39:07.510
You are mine to toy with.

393
00:39:07.590 --> 00:39:11.100
Forward!

394
00:39:11.180 --> 00:39:14.970
- Gimme the rope.

395
00:39:15.060 --> 00:39:19.060
Where-
Where...

396
00:39:19.150 --> 00:39:21.440
did you get that baby?

397
00:39:21.480 --> 00:39:26.240
I stole it from a stupid Daikini.

398
00:39:26.400 --> 00:39:29.570
Franjean. release the Nelwyns.

399
00:39:29.610 --> 00:39:33.910
-And stop pestering them.
- Uh-oh.

400
00:39:33.990 --> 00:39:36.080
Ahh-

401
00:39:38.330 --> 00:39:40.290
- Yaah!

402
00:39:44.550 --> 00:39:47.800
- You!

403
00:39:47.840 --> 00:39:52.930
Welcome to my kingdom.

404
00:39:59.100 --> 00:40:03.610
- I'm happy to meet you. Willow Ufgood.
- How do you know my name?

405
00:40:03.690 --> 00:40:06.940
Blora Danan told me.

406
00:40:06.990 --> 00:40:10.320
Blora?
Blora. Willow is here.

407
00:40:13.120 --> 00:40:18.660
- But she's just a baby.
- She's very special.

408
00:40:18.750 --> 00:40:24.090
My Brownies have been searching for her
ever since we heard she was born.

409
00:40:24.170 --> 00:40:29.090
Blora Danan has chosen you
to be her guardian.

410
00:40:29.170 --> 00:40:33.930
- Me?
- Yes. She likes you.

411
00:40:35.350 --> 00:40:40.310
And Elora Danan knows you
have the courage to help us.

412
00:40:40.390 --> 00:40:43.980
Take my wand
to the sorceress. Find Raziel.

413
00:40:44.060 --> 00:40:48.320
She will guide you and Blora Danan
to the kingdom of Tir Asleen.

414
00:40:48.360 --> 00:40:51.490
where a good king and queen
will look after her.

415
00:40:51.530 --> 00:40:55.330
You need a warrior for
a job like this. I'm a nobody.

416
00:40:55.490 --> 00:40:58.750
Blora. you don't want me.

417
00:40:58.830 --> 00:41:02.540
Tell her.
I'm short. even for a Nelwyn.

418
00:41:05.500 --> 00:41:08.130
Hello?

419
00:41:15.470 --> 00:41:18.890
Blora Danan must survive!

420
00:41:18.930 --> 00:41:23.810
She must fulfill her destiny and bring
about the downfall of Queen Bavmorda.

421
00:41:23.850 --> 00:41:26.730
whose powers are growing
like an evil plague.

422
00:41:26.770 --> 00:41:31.150
Unless she is stopped.
Bavmorda will control the lives...

423
00:41:31.190 --> 00:41:35.780
of your village.
your children- everyone.

424
00:41:40.450 --> 00:41:43.960
All creatures of good heart
need your help. Willow.

425
00:41:44.040 --> 00:41:49.250
The choice is yours.

426
00:42:11.820 --> 00:42:16.070
- Hey. Meegosh. Wake up.
- Huh?

427
00:42:16.110 --> 00:42:20.370
- It's time to go home.
- Home?

428
00:42:22.950 --> 00:42:26.500
Listen. Meegosh.
Tell Kiaya I love her.

429
00:42:26.580 --> 00:42:31.130
- And I think of her every day.
- Willow-

430
00:42:31.210 --> 00:42:34.670
And tell her I'm not going to let
anything happen to the baby.

431
00:42:34.760 --> 00:42:37.390
Are you sure you know
what you're doing?

432
00:42:37.470 --> 00:42:40.390
I hope so.

433
00:42:40.470 --> 00:42:44.060
Listen. be careful.

434
00:42:50.150 --> 00:42:54.690
- I know the way. Franjean.
- You always think you know the way.

435
00:42:54.780 --> 00:42:58.240
-I am the leader!
- How long will it take to find Raziel?

436
00:42:58.320 --> 00:43:02.790
Um. not long. She's been exiled
to an island just over those hills.

437
00:43:02.870 --> 00:43:05.960
- She's what?
- Exiled...

438
00:43:06.040 --> 00:43:09.880
by the evil Queen Bavmorda.

439
00:43:09.960 --> 00:43:12.590
Rool. You fool. He does
not need to know everything.

440
00:43:12.670 --> 00:43:15.260
- I didn't tell him everything.
- You told him enough.

441
00:43:15.340 --> 00:43:17.630
- You mentioned the island. the queen.
- Wait a minute.

442
00:43:17.680 --> 00:43:20.350
So?

443
00:43:20.430 --> 00:43:23.220
What do you mean? What are
you saying. mysterious island?

444
00:43:23.310 --> 00:43:25.930
Don't play with that wand.

445
00:43:25.980 --> 00:43:28.560
Cherlindrea told you
it holds vast powers.

446
00:43:28.650 --> 00:43:31.110
Only a great sorcerer can use it.

447
00:43:31.190 --> 00:43:33.940
-Not a stupid peck like you.

448
00:43:33.980 --> 00:43:37.150
- This way.
- No. No. No. I don't think so.

449
00:43:37.240 --> 00:43:39.530
- All right. then this way.
- Bah. nope.

450
00:43:39.610 --> 00:43:42.120
- This way.
- This way?

451
00:43:42.200 --> 00:43:45.950
- That's what I said.
- This way.

452
00:43:46.000 --> 00:43:49.460
- You know where you're going?
- Of course.

453
00:43:49.540 --> 00:43:52.250
With us as your guides
no harm with befall you.

454
00:44:02.680 --> 00:44:06.850
- Take it up!

455
00:44:08.350 --> 00:44:12.610
- We are not going in there!
- But Blora needs fresh milk.

456
00:44:12.690 --> 00:44:17.530
- And we are drenched.
- You are not in command. shorty. I am!

457
00:44:17.610 --> 00:44:21.200
- You hear me?
- Whoa!

458
00:44:58.940 --> 00:45:01.400
- Excuse me? Excuse me.

459
00:45:01.450 --> 00:45:04.410
Could you spare some milk
for this poor. hungry baby?

460
00:45:04.490 --> 00:45:06.370
Get out of here. peck!

461
00:45:06.450 --> 00:45:08.790
Get outta here
or we'll cook ya!

462
00:45:22.180 --> 00:45:26.100
Ooh. look at her!

463
00:45:26.140 --> 00:45:28.430
I could use
a love potion on her!

464
00:45:28.470 --> 00:45:32.310
Franjean! Hey! Give me that
dust of broken heart.

465
00:45:32.390 --> 00:45:34.100
- Come on! Give it to me!
- Let go of me!

466
00:45:34.190 --> 00:45:37.570
It's very dangerous.
It belongs to the fairies!

467
00:45:41.740 --> 00:45:43.740
Hey. quiet!
You want to get us killed?

468
00:45:50.700 --> 00:45:54.460
Oh. Rool! Always playing
with those fairy love potions.

469
00:45:56.750 --> 00:46:01.880
You are so beautiful!

470
00:46:01.970 --> 00:46:05.590
- Your eyes! Your whiskers!

471
00:46:05.680 --> 00:46:08.300
- I have to kiss you!
-Rool!

472
00:46:08.390 --> 00:46:10.140
That dust of broken heart!

473
00:46:24.990 --> 00:46:27.200
Beer!

474
00:46:30.330 --> 00:46:32.450
These people are crazy!
This could be bad!

475
00:46:37.040 --> 00:46:39.040
Hurry! Hurry!

476
00:46:39.130 --> 00:46:41.000
My husband's coming!

477
00:46:41.090 --> 00:46:43.130
If he catches you here.
he'll kill us both!

478
00:46:43.210 --> 00:46:45.840
- How do I look?
- Not you!

479
00:46:47.050 --> 00:46:48.970
Where the hell
did you come from?

480
00:46:49.050 --> 00:46:51.310
I knew I shouldn't
have trusted you.

481
00:46:51.350 --> 00:46:55.190
Don't I know you?
I stole the baby from you. Daikini.

482
00:46:55.270 --> 00:46:57.480
- While you were taking a pee-pee!
- Cover your face!

483
00:46:57.560 --> 00:47:01.190
- You are crawling with Brownies.
- I hate Brownies!

484
00:47:01.230 --> 00:47:04.070
Whoa!

485
00:47:04.150 --> 00:47:06.740
- Where is he? Where?
- Hello. dear.

486
00:47:06.820 --> 00:47:09.200
There's nobody here but
me and. uh. my. uh-

487
00:47:09.240 --> 00:47:11.660
- I'll kill him!
- ...my cousin. Hilda.

488
00:47:11.740 --> 00:47:14.000
- Hilda?
- Hilda.

489
00:47:14.040 --> 00:47:16.160
- Oh. Hilda!
- This is my husband. Llug.

490
00:47:16.250 --> 00:47:19.000
- Mmm... Big husband.
- Yes.

491
00:47:19.080 --> 00:47:20.920
- How do you do?

492
00:47:21.000 --> 00:47:23.380
Hilda! Ooh.

493
00:47:23.420 --> 00:47:25.550
Come on. girly.
Don't be shy.

494
00:47:25.630 --> 00:47:28.260
- Hey! Give her back!

495
00:47:28.340 --> 00:47:30.720
- Pecks make terrible nursemaids.
- Nursemaid?

496
00:47:30.800 --> 00:47:33.720
- They get too excited.

497
00:47:33.770 --> 00:47:36.390
Excuse me!
Are we having a party?

498
00:47:36.480 --> 00:47:38.520
- Huh?
- Hey. hey. hey. hey!

499
00:47:38.600 --> 00:47:43.230
- Stop. please. Ooh.

500
00:47:43.320 --> 00:47:45.190
Come on.
Fight like a man!

501
00:47:45.240 --> 00:47:48.280
- Want to breed?

502
00:47:48.360 --> 00:47:51.370
Tempting. but no.

503
00:47:54.290 --> 00:47:56.250
Thank you.
Time to leave.

504
00:47:56.290 --> 00:47:58.250
- Bye. Hilda!
- Take them out.

505
00:47:58.290 --> 00:48:01.460
- Hey! Come along!

506
00:48:01.540 --> 00:48:04.130
- Careful. you lout!
- Move along!

507
00:48:04.210 --> 00:48:06.920
Gather pall these babies.

508
00:48:07.010 --> 00:48:09.260
That baby over there.
Let me see its arm.

509
00:48:13.010 --> 00:48:15.140
That's not the one.

510
00:48:18.850 --> 00:48:21.600
You! Are you the mother
of that child?

511
00:48:21.690 --> 00:48:24.270
- Yes. Yes. I am.
- Let me see it.

512
00:48:24.360 --> 00:48:25.940
No! Don't let her!

513
00:48:26.030 --> 00:48:27.490
Aah!

514
00:48:27.570 --> 00:48:30.450
I gave you an order. woman!

515
00:48:39.790 --> 00:48:43.250
You-
You're... beautiful.

516
00:48:43.340 --> 00:48:46.670
- And you're very strong.
- Thank you.

517
00:48:49.260 --> 00:48:51.760
You're no woman!

518
00:48:51.840 --> 00:48:53.680
- Now. honey. take it easy.
- Not a woman?

519
00:48:53.760 --> 00:48:56.640
- Gentlemen.
- Not a woman?

520
00:48:56.680 --> 00:48:59.480
- Meet Llug.

521
00:49:00.770 --> 00:49:02.810
- After them!
- Out of the way!

522
00:49:09.110 --> 00:49:10.360
- To the horses!

523
00:49:10.360 --> 00:49:11.450
- To the horses!

524
00:49:13.990 --> 00:49:16.450
Hey! What are you doing?

525
00:49:20.830 --> 00:49:22.750
- Hyah!

526
00:49:22.830 --> 00:49:26.750
Madmartigan!
Madmartigan! Wait!

527
00:49:30.220 --> 00:49:35.100
- He's not a woman!
- To your horses! Hyah! Hyah!

528
00:49:35.180 --> 00:49:37.560
Don't let them get away!

529
00:49:39.220 --> 00:49:42.640
- Madmartigan. stop!
- What?

530
00:49:54.450 --> 00:49:56.490
Hyah!

531
00:50:01.620 --> 00:50:04.120
Madmartigan.
I'm warning you-

532
00:50:06.170 --> 00:50:09.840
- Ow!
- Prepare to die!

533
00:50:33.240 --> 00:50:35.570
Madmartigan!
Stop!

534
00:51:05.640 --> 00:51:07.690
Franjean. help me!

535
00:51:12.320 --> 00:51:14.240
- Rool!
- Help!

536
00:51:14.320 --> 00:51:17.360
Rool! Rool.

537
00:51:18.530 --> 00:51:22.330
- Rool! What are you doing?
- Help me!

538
00:51:27.710 --> 00:51:29.960
- Come on. I am.
- Pull me in.

539
00:51:30.040 --> 00:51:32.500
Yeah. pull!

540
00:51:50.690 --> 00:51:52.690
You can't have her!

541
00:51:58.610 --> 00:52:00.320
Whoa!

542
00:52:05.040 --> 00:52:08.620
- Rool. this isn't funny!

543
00:52:08.710 --> 00:52:10.630
Help me cut the rope!

544
00:52:23.810 --> 00:52:26.560
Who-oa!

545
00:52:48.080 --> 00:52:50.670
Willow. stay down!

546
00:52:54.380 --> 00:52:56.420
Whoa!

547
00:52:56.460 --> 00:52:58.720
Whoa!

548
00:52:58.800 --> 00:53:00.720
Gone crazy?

549
00:53:00.800 --> 00:53:02.930
You can't chase around
with Elora like this.

550
00:53:03.010 --> 00:53:05.430
- We're getting off!
- Hyah!

551
00:53:05.470 --> 00:53:08.100
Oh! Hold on! Hyah!

552
00:53:30.910 --> 00:53:33.420
Whoa! Whoa!

553
00:53:36.590 --> 00:53:38.920
- Oh. Rool.

554
00:53:39.010 --> 00:53:42.680
Now we stop. peck.

555
00:53:42.760 --> 00:53:48.060
Stupid Daikini.
Ask him to stop the wagon.

556
00:53:48.100 --> 00:53:52.310
Madmartigan! You never. ever
drive that fast with an infant!

557
00:53:53.810 --> 00:53:56.310
I just saved that infant's life!

558
00:53:57.770 --> 00:54:00.110
Hah! Hah!

559
00:54:00.190 --> 00:54:02.150
Gather your wits. Come on.

560
00:54:02.200 --> 00:54:05.240
- Don't wory about me.
-Come on!

561
00:54:06.320 --> 00:54:08.490
- Get down!

562
00:54:08.580 --> 00:54:10.950
Uh. where am I?
Oh!

563
00:54:12.870 --> 00:54:14.960
Rool. you fool.
get out of the road!

564
00:54:31.470 --> 00:54:34.060
-Ah. Franjean!
- You better clear out. Willow.

565
00:54:34.140 --> 00:54:35.600
Before those troops come back.

566
00:54:35.650 --> 00:54:39.110
- Ah. my head!
- We don't need him. Blora.

567
00:54:47.530 --> 00:54:49.620
Madmartigan. wait!

568
00:54:49.660 --> 00:54:53.000
Go home. Willow!
It's a dangerous world.

569
00:54:53.080 --> 00:54:55.040
Yeah. and that's why
we need your help.

570
00:54:55.120 --> 00:54:58.340
My help? What do you need my help for?

571
00:54:58.420 --> 00:55:00.590
You're a sorcerer!

572
00:55:00.670 --> 00:55:03.880
You're a great warrior.
and a swordsman.

573
00:55:03.970 --> 00:55:06.840
And you're ten times
bigger than I am. stupid!

574
00:55:06.930 --> 00:55:10.180
Are you tying to make my life
more difficult than it already is?

575
00:55:13.430 --> 00:55:18.360
- Hurry! Big dogs!

576
00:55:18.440 --> 00:55:22.690
Look. I'm sorry
I got angry.

577
00:55:22.730 --> 00:55:24.690
We wouldn't have
escaped without you.

578
00:55:38.880 --> 00:55:41.710
Well. don't expect me
to help you again.

579
00:55:43.210 --> 00:55:46.840
Good! Then we go that way!
To the lake!

580
00:55:47.880 --> 00:55:51.050
That way.

581
00:55:51.100 --> 00:55:54.720
You are drunk. and when you
are drunk you forget that...

582
00:55:54.810 --> 00:55:56.730
- I am in charge!
- You are in charge.

583
00:55:56.810 --> 00:55:59.020
Fine.
Then which way do we go?

584
00:55:59.100 --> 00:56:01.110
That way!

585
00:56:04.150 --> 00:56:08.700
Oh. no!
That's the way I'm going.

586
00:56:08.740 --> 00:56:11.740
All right. all right. You can
follow me as far as the lake.

587
00:56:11.830 --> 00:56:14.040
But that's it!

588
00:56:14.080 --> 00:56:17.870
- You're not going south. are you?
- No. just as far as the lake.

589
00:56:17.910 --> 00:56:23.090
Good. Mumbo-Jumbo. I am hungry.
Go and get me some eggs or something.

590
00:56:23.170 --> 00:56:25.800
- We are not afraid of you!
- Now!

591
00:56:32.510 --> 00:56:37.180
Kael. have you found the child?

592
00:56:37.270 --> 00:56:39.020
The search goes on. my queen.

593
00:56:40.100 --> 00:56:42.110
Why. with my powers.

594
00:56:42.190 --> 00:56:45.400
with the strength
of my great army.

595
00:56:45.480 --> 00:56:48.900
can you not find
one little child?

596
00:56:48.950 --> 00:56:51.280
We look even now.
It won't be long.

597
00:56:51.360 --> 00:56:54.740
Find the child.
Find the child!

598
00:56:54.780 --> 00:56:57.410
Time is running out.

599
00:57:01.580 --> 00:57:06.000
- Good night.

600
00:57:06.050 --> 00:57:09.380
She is kinda cute.

601
00:57:09.470 --> 00:57:11.220
When she's quiet.

602
00:57:12.640 --> 00:57:14.550
She's really a princess.

603
00:57:14.640 --> 00:57:18.640
Really?
And you're a great sorcerer.

604
00:57:18.730 --> 00:57:20.640
And I'm the king of Cashmere.

605
00:57:20.730 --> 00:57:24.520
Go to sleep. Willow.

606
00:57:24.610 --> 00:57:27.110
Good night. Madmartigan.

607
00:57:27.150 --> 00:57:30.150
Rats! Big rats! Rats!

608
00:57:30.200 --> 00:57:33.530
Uh- Uh! Oh!
Rats! Ra-

609
00:57:33.620 --> 00:57:36.530
Oh. Rool. you had
that stupid rat dream!

610
00:57:47.340 --> 00:57:50.050
Tuatha...

611
00:57:50.130 --> 00:57:52.300
Lawkathok...

612
00:57:52.380 --> 00:57:54.300
- Tuatha!

613
00:57:54.340 --> 00:57:57.100
Huh?
Willow?

614
00:57:58.180 --> 00:58:00.310
Willow?

615
00:58:02.060 --> 00:58:04.520
Oh. There you are.

616
00:58:04.600 --> 00:58:06.560
Madmartigan!

617
00:58:06.650 --> 00:58:09.980
'Night. Willow.

618
00:58:22.080 --> 00:58:24.080
This way! This way!

619
00:58:35.890 --> 00:58:37.850
What are you doing?

620
00:58:37.890 --> 00:58:40.270
I found some black root.
She loves it!

621
00:58:40.350 --> 00:58:43.270
Black root? I am
the father of two children.

622
00:58:43.350 --> 00:58:45.350
and you never. ever
give a baby black root.

623
00:58:45.520 --> 00:58:48.570
Well. my mother
raised us on black root.

624
00:58:48.650 --> 00:58:51.190
It's good for ya!
It puts hair on your chest.

625
00:58:51.280 --> 00:58:54.030
- Doesn't it. Sticks?
- Her name is not Sticks.

626
00:58:54.070 --> 00:58:57.030
She's Blora Danan.
the future empress of Tir Asleen.

627
00:58:57.070 --> 00:58:59.410
And the last thing she's gonna
want is a hairy chest!

628
00:59:03.580 --> 00:59:05.620
Did you see what he did?

629
00:59:05.710 --> 00:59:08.960
He stole our black root. I'll get
some more. don't wory about it.

630
00:59:13.800 --> 00:59:17.140
- There it is! The island!

631
00:59:19.350 --> 00:59:21.260
We made it.

632
00:59:21.350 --> 00:59:25.890
We have led you to
the island of the sorceress Fin Raziel.

633
00:59:25.980 --> 00:59:30.230
- We'll get a boat in that village.
- A big boat. 

634
00:59:48.290 --> 00:59:50.290
Well. looks like
I got you here.

635
00:59:50.380 --> 00:59:52.840
You!
What did you do?

636
00:59:52.920 --> 00:59:55.920
All you did was hang around
and eat our eggs! Huh?

637
00:59:56.010 --> 00:59:57.970
I found a boat.
We're all set.

638
00:59:58.050 --> 01:00:01.970
Good. Take these two lizards
out and drown them.

639
01:00:02.060 --> 01:00:05.390
- Who are you calling lizards?
- Heh? Heh?

640
01:00:07.480 --> 01:00:10.150
Your mother was lizard!

641
01:00:13.150 --> 01:00:15.650
- Good-bye. Sticks.

642
01:00:18.320 --> 01:00:21.240
If you really are a princess.

643
01:00:21.320 --> 01:00:24.290
take care of him.

644
01:00:30.630 --> 01:00:33.920
- Madmartigan!
- What?

645
01:00:34.000 --> 01:00:35.880
Thanks.

646
01:00:45.390 --> 01:00:47.930
Hey! Aah!

647
01:00:47.980 --> 01:00:51.350
-Keep walkin'. hero!
- Don't even turnaround!

648
01:00:52.520 --> 01:00:55.530
- It's all right. Blora.

649
01:00:55.610 --> 01:00:58.030
- Go to sleep.

650
01:00:58.110 --> 01:01:00.450
- Nobody'll find you here.

651
01:01:00.530 --> 01:01:02.120
I'll be back with
Fin Raziel very soon.

652
01:01:02.160 --> 01:01:05.490
We will guard her
with our meager lives.

653
01:01:33.810 --> 01:01:36.650
Raziel!

654
01:01:36.730 --> 01:01:40.530
Fin Raziel!
I have to talk to you. please!

655
01:01:44.450 --> 01:01:47.040
Raziel!

656
01:01:51.870 --> 01:01:55.540
She's not here.

657
01:01:58.550 --> 01:02:00.470
- Aah!

658
01:02:00.550 --> 01:02:04.090
Get back! Who are you?

659
01:02:05.220 --> 01:02:08.100
Who are you?

660
01:02:10.520 --> 01:02:13.600
- I'm Willow Ufgood.
- What are you doing here?

661
01:02:13.690 --> 01:02:17.360
I've come to find the great
sorceress. Fin Raziel.

662
01:02:17.440 --> 01:02:20.030
That's me!
I'm Raziel!

663
01:02:22.070 --> 01:02:23.990
This can't be right!

664
01:02:24.070 --> 01:02:27.580
One of Bavmorda's spells
transformed me.

665
01:02:29.870 --> 01:02:32.460
Believe me. it could
have been worse!

666
01:02:32.540 --> 01:02:38.340
Oh. Well. this wand is for you.
It's from Cherlindrea.

667
01:02:38.420 --> 01:02:42.920
Then the prophecy is true.
The princess has been born.

668
01:02:43.010 --> 01:02:44.970
Take me to her.

669
01:02:47.510 --> 01:02:50.270
It is Blora Danan.

670
01:02:50.350 --> 01:02:53.270
Isn't she beautiful?

671
01:02:53.350 --> 01:02:56.310
Isn't she beautiful?

672
01:02:56.400 --> 01:02:59.900
- That's Raziel?
- I don't know. I-

673
01:02:59.980 --> 01:03:02.240
I expected something
more grand. Less. uh-

674
01:03:02.280 --> 01:03:04.240
- Fuzzy.
- Fuzzy!

675
01:03:04.320 --> 01:03:08.120
You must use the wand.
Turn me back into my human form.

676
01:03:08.200 --> 01:03:11.540
- What do I do?
- You mean you're not a sorcerer?

677
01:03:12.750 --> 01:03:15.250
Yes. Sort a.

678
01:03:15.330 --> 01:03:17.830
-I'm a farmer.

679
01:03:17.920 --> 01:03:19.840
But I do know a few tricks.

680
01:03:19.880 --> 01:03:25.430
Tricks? Cherlindrea sent you?
You must learn real magic.

681
01:03:25.550 --> 01:03:29.600
- Horses! Horses!

682
01:03:29.680 --> 01:03:32.180
Quick! Take her!
Hurry! Hurry!

683
01:03:40.980 --> 01:03:43.940
I knew he was a traitor!

684
01:03:46.530 --> 01:03:49.240
- Sorry about this. peck.
- Keep your mouth shut!

685
01:03:50.280 --> 01:03:53.080
Told you we'd find him
without your help.

686
01:03:53.160 --> 01:03:55.120
- Give me that baby.
- No!

687
01:03:58.580 --> 01:04:02.550
- Give her back!
- Leave me alone! Don't touch me!

688
01:04:08.470 --> 01:04:10.350
This is the one
we're looking for.

689
01:04:10.430 --> 01:04:13.810
- We must take it back to Nockmaar.

690
01:04:16.600 --> 01:04:18.520
Lose your skirt?

691
01:04:26.190 --> 01:04:28.150
I've still got what counts.

692
01:04:28.200 --> 01:04:30.530
Not for long.

693
01:04:36.370 --> 01:04:39.920
- Bring him.
- Over here!

694
01:04:57.600 --> 01:05:00.350
We'll never keep up
with those horses.

695
01:05:00.400 --> 01:05:02.360
Then we will
have to track them.

696
01:05:02.400 --> 01:05:03.820
That would take forever.

697
01:05:03.900 --> 01:05:06.650
Besides. even if we find them.
they'll catch us.

698
01:05:06.690 --> 01:05:09.900
stick us in cages. torture us
and finally devour us.

699
01:05:09.990 --> 01:05:11.950
Are you suggesting
we go home?

700
01:05:12.030 --> 01:05:14.950
- Nah. This is more fun!
- All right.

701
01:05:15.040 --> 01:05:16.950
Fine. then.
Come on!

702
01:05:30.760 --> 01:05:34.220
I'm worried about Blora.
She doesn't sound good.

703
01:05:34.260 --> 01:05:37.060
Hurry! Practice
the chant I taught you!

704
01:05:37.100 --> 01:05:42.900
- Tanna... looatha- Oh. I can't
remember the middle part.

705
01:05:42.980 --> 01:05:45.020
Locktwaar!

706
01:05:45.070 --> 01:05:48.070
That's the word
that pleads for change.

707
01:05:48.150 --> 01:05:50.110
Locktwaar.

708
01:05:53.780 --> 01:05:56.950
Blora's cold and hungry.
She knows me.

709
01:05:57.040 --> 01:05:58.950
Please. let me
take care of her.

710
01:05:59.040 --> 01:06:01.160
I don't need help
from a peck.

711
01:06:04.920 --> 01:06:08.960
- What are you staring at?
- Your leg.

712
01:06:09.050 --> 01:06:11.420
I'd like to break it.

713
01:06:11.470 --> 01:06:16.350
You may find that difficult while
I'm up here and you're down there.

714
01:06:19.470 --> 01:06:21.690
I hate that woman.

715
01:06:54.340 --> 01:06:56.430
Hyah!

716
01:07:00.220 --> 01:07:03.020
- I found it. Kael.

717
01:07:04.140 --> 01:07:07.190
That should make
my mother happy.

718
01:07:07.270 --> 01:07:10.280
What are they gonna do to her?

719
01:07:22.830 --> 01:07:25.500
Hither walha...

720
01:07:25.580 --> 01:07:29.130
bairn derubordak...

721
01:07:29.210 --> 01:07:31.130
- bellanockt.

722
01:07:31.210 --> 01:07:34.090
That's magic?
Smells terrible.

723
01:07:34.170 --> 01:07:37.390
- It's the life spark. It forms after-
- Well. it stinks!

724
01:07:37.470 --> 01:07:40.640
- This whole thing stinks!
- Ignore him. Willow.

725
01:07:40.720 --> 01:07:43.730
- He's a fool!
- If only I had a sword!

726
01:07:43.810 --> 01:07:46.900
- If only you'd quit talking about it.

727
01:07:46.980 --> 01:07:50.360
Willow. you must transform me
to my human self.

728
01:07:50.400 --> 01:07:53.230
But. Raziel.
I'm not ready yet.

729
01:07:53.320 --> 01:07:56.530
You'd better be.
Get me down.

730
01:08:00.160 --> 01:08:02.580
Ow!

731
01:08:05.210 --> 01:08:08.210
Why don't you help me get out of here
instead of chattering with that muskrat?

732
01:08:08.290 --> 01:08:11.040
Muskrat!
When I change back...

733
01:08:11.090 --> 01:08:15.050
to my former self.
I will crush this army.

734
01:08:15.130 --> 01:08:17.800
and take Blora Danan
to Tir Asleen...

735
01:08:17.880 --> 01:08:20.470
where she will be safe.

736
01:08:20.550 --> 01:08:22.890
- Ow!

737
01:08:22.930 --> 01:08:24.890
What'd you bite me for?

738
01:08:24.930 --> 01:08:28.270
You need three drops
of your blood to put in the potion.

739
01:08:28.350 --> 01:08:31.650
- Well. you coulda warned me.

740
01:08:31.730 --> 01:08:34.150
For beginners.
there's some pain.

741
01:08:34.230 --> 01:08:39.320
but don't let anything
break your concentration.

742
01:08:44.450 --> 01:08:47.330
Hit her green anbairn
claideblunanockt.

